results.question: According to Medicare, the 'Three-Day Payment Window Rule' refers to:

choices.A: The time frame in which a patient must pay their bill
choices.B: Services provided to a patient 3 days prior to their inpatient admission
choices.C: The time frame in which Medicare must process a claim
choices.D: The period within which a patient can dispute a charge

results.reasoning: The 'Three-Day Payment Window Rule' under Medicare refers to the requirement that all outpatient diagnostic services and related non-diagnostic services provided to a patient within three days prior to an inpatient admission must be included in the inpatient claim. This rule ensures that services closely related to the inpatient stay are billed together, preventing separate billing for services that are part of the same episode of care.
